history.content:
When I took the class (with Babak Spring 20), it was almost weekly homeworks (8 homeworks?) and about 5-6 Juypter Notebook labs. 3 midterms in class with no finals.  There are no physical labs you have to attend. I would classify it as a low-medium workload class.

I'm not too sure if Babak is teaching next semester in the Spring, but if he is, I HIGHLY recommened it. I, alongside several of my friends, left the class feeling like it was the best class I've ever taken at Cal in terms of the quality of instruction, the way the material was presented, and its applications to the real world. If you ever want to do anything in EE, this is the foundational course you MUST take. Babak's 2 hour lectures were incredible just to be in them and I distinctly remember the lecture was almost always full during the 4-6 pm block (which tells you something).
